(72, 'Minecraft', 'Ad Info\r\nEnchantment Table\r\nEnchantment Table.png\r\nEnchantment Table\r\nType	\r\nSolid Block\r\nRequirements	\r\nNone\r\nPhysics	\r\nNo\r\nTransparency	\r\nYes\r\nLuminance	\r\nNo\r\nBlast resistance	\r\n6,000\r\nTool	\r\nA wooden pickaxe or better is required to mine this block\r\nRenewable	\r\nNo\r\nStackable	\r\nYes (64)\r\nFlammable	\r\nNo\r\nFirst appearance	\r\nBeta 1.9pre3\r\nTile Entity ID	\r\nEnchantTable\r\nData value	\r\ndec: 116 hex: 74 bin: 1110100\r\nName	\r\nenchanting_table\r\nAn enchantment table is a block that allows players to spend their experience point levels to enchant tools, books and armor. Enchanting works in three stages.[1][2] The sprites and icons of enchanted items have a purple luminescence.\r\nThe table will enchant all tools and armor except the hoe, shears, and horse armor. The hoe and shears cannot be enchanted by the enchantment table and require an anvil and an appropriate enchanted book.\r\nIf the table is surrounded by bookshelves, with one block of air in between, arcane glyphs float from the bookshelves into the book (if particles are turned on). Having bookshelves near an enchantment table will increase the potency of enchantments.[3]\r\nThe enchantment table is 3⁄4 blocks high.', '2014-04-12 18:48:47'),
